                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>6</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="90030" author="yujian" created="Fri, 25 Jul 2014 06:33:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for master branch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/11226&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/11226&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="89429" author="adilger" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2014 23:49:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The current implementation on the MDS is that if a pool name doesn&apos;t exist, the file will be created in the default pool.  This is to avoid problems creating files if e.g. a default striping is set on a directory with a specific pool but the pool is later removed.  Rather than making the userspace validation more robust (which adds overhead and can always be defeated), it would be better to handle this differently on the MDS and return an error (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;-ENXIO&lt;/tt&gt; or whatever) if the pool does not exist.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="89423" author="pjones" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2014 22:00:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yu, Jian&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please assist with this issue?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
